## Socket Events

| Event | Direction | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `queue:join` | Client → Server | Enter matchmaking |
| `queue:leave` | Client → Server | Cancel matchmaking |
| `queue:joined` | Server → Client | Confirmation |
| `match:found` | Server → Client | Room + color assigned |
| `game:move` | Client → Server | Submit move |
| `game:update` | Server → Client | New FEN + state |
| `game:over` | Server → Client | Result + ratings |
| `game:state` | Server → Client | Full state (reconnect) |
| `game:resign` | Client → Server | Forfeit |
| `online:update` | Server → All | Online count |

**Socket auth:** Pass JWT in `socket.handshake.auth.token`

---

## Key Security Properties

- Passwords hashed with bcrypt (12 rounds)  
- JWT verified on every request AND every socket connection  
- User identity **only** from JWT — never from client payload  
- Move legality validated server-side with chess.js  
- Auth endpoints rate-limited to 10 req / 15 min
- `passwordHash` never appears in any API response (Mongoose transform)
- Body size limited to 10kb
- Helmet security headers applied
- NoSQL injection sanitization active

